    Inspired by a string of numbers, yield a tuple formatted with cnumbers divided on underscores, if no underscores exist in the phrase you should join on semicolons ';' if no semicolons are present you should return the total count of uppercase letters in even positions in the alphabet, ord('A') = 1, ord('B') = 2, ... ord('Z') = 26
    Examples
    split_words("Hello world!") ➞ ["Hello", "world!"]
